DanceNBearz wrote:
>
> what causes swaying...?

starting with all the front end stuff,, and not forgetting the rear torsion rubbers and rear
diagonal arm bushings,

also, don't forget the tire sidewall ratings,,,


tires.. sidewall too weak,
wheel bearings loose
ball joints,
tie rod ends, including drag link
loose center pivot bushing/ pin
steering box loose
torsion bushings tight or loose , not greased

rear torsion rubber bushings,
rear diagonal arm bushings

shocks

sway bar missing or broken

etcetera!
